anceps: hu*c mo_ns e^t i_llu*c ce^ci^di^t e_t ru*pt(o) a_gge^re*

speaker: ['#megara']
perseus: nova cucurrit Thessalus torrens via:
anceps: no*va_ cu^cu_rri*t the_ssa^lu_s to*rre_ns vi^a*

speaker: ['#megara']
perseus: talis, parentes liberos patriam petens,
anceps: ta*li_s pa^re_nte*s li_be^ro_s pa^tri^a_m pe^te*ns

speaker: ['#megara']
perseus: erumpe rerum terminos tecum efferens,
anceps: e*ru_mpe^ re_ru*m te_rmi^no_s te*c(u)m e_ffe^re*ns

speaker: ['#megara']
perseus: et quicquid avida tot per annorum gradus
anceps: e*t qvi_dqvi^d a^vi^da* to_t pe^r a_nno*ru_m gra^du*s

speaker: ['#megara']
perseus: abscondit aetas redde et oblitos sui
anceps: a*bsco_ndi^t [ae]ta*s re_dd(e) e^t o_bli*to_s su^i*

speaker: ['#megara']
perseus: lucisque pavidos ante te populos age.
anceps: lu*ci_sqve^ pa^vi^do*s a_nte^ te_ po^pu^lo_s a^ge*

speaker: ['#megara']
perseus: indigna te sunt spolia, si tantum refers
anceps: i*ndi_gna^ te_ su*nt spo^li^a^ si_ ta*ntu_m re^fe*rs

speaker: ['#megara']
perseus: quantum imperatum est. magna sed nimium loquor
anceps: qva*nt(u)m i_mpe^ra_t(u)m e*st ma_gna^ se_d ni^mi^u_m lo^qvo*r

speaker: ['#megara']
perseus: ignara nostrae sortis, unde illum mihi
anceps: i*gna_ra^ no_str[ae] so_rti^s u_nd(e) i*llu_m mi^hi*

speaker: ['#megara']
perseus: quo te tuamque dexteram amplectar diem
anceps: qvo* te_ tu^a_mqve* de_xte^r(a)m a_mple*cta_r di^e*m

speaker: ['#megara']
perseus: reditusque lentos nec mei memores querar?
anceps: re^di^tu_sqve^ le_nto*s ne_c me^i_ me^mo^re_s qve^ra*r

speaker: ['#megara']
perseus: tibi, o deorum ductor, indomiti ferent
anceps: tu*m ti^bi^ de^o_ru*m du_cto^r i_ndo^mi^ti_ fe^re*nt

speaker: ['#megara']
perseus: centena tauri colla; tibi, frugum potens,
anceps: ce*nte_na^ t[au]ri* co_lla^ ti^bi^ fru*gu_m po^te*ns

speaker: ['#megara']
perseus: secreta reddam sacra: tibi muta fide
anceps: se*cre_ta^ re_dda*m sa_cra^ ti^bi^ mu*ta_ fi^de*

speaker: ['#megara']
perseus: longas Eleusin tacita iactabit faces,
anceps: lo*nga_s e^le_vsi*n ta^ci^ta^ ja_cta*bi_t fa^ce*s

speaker: ['#megara']
perseus: tum restitutas fratribus rebor meis
anceps: tu*m re_sti^tu_ta*s fra_tri^bu_s re*bo_r me^i*s

speaker: ['#megara']
perseus: animas et ipsum regna moderantem sua
anceps: a^ni^ma_s e^t i_psu*m re_gna^ mo^de^ra*nte_m su^a*

speaker: ['#megara']
perseus: florere patrem, si qua te maior tenet
anceps: flo*re_re^ pa_tre*m si_ qva^ te_ ma*jo_r te^ne*t

speaker: ['#megara']
perseus: clausum potestas, sequimur: aut omnes tuo
anceps: cl[au]su_m po^te_sta*s se^qvi^mu^r [au]t o*mni_s tu^o*

speaker: ['#megara']
perseus: defende reditu sospes aut omnes trahe.
anceps: de*fe_nde^ re^di^tu* so_spe^s [au]t o*mne_s tra^he*

speaker: ['#megara']
perseus: trahes nec ullus eriget fractos deus.
anceps: tra*he_s ne^c u_llu*s e_ri^ge_t fra*cto_s de^u*s

speaker: ['#amphitryon']
perseus: O socia nostri sanguinis, casta fide
anceps: o* so^ci^a^ no_stri* sa_ngvi^ni_s ca*sta_ fi^de*

speaker: ['#amphitryon']
perseus: servans torum natosque magnanimi Herculis,
anceps: se*rva_ns to^ru_m gna*to_sqve^ ma_gna^ni^m(i) he_rcu^li*s

speaker: ['#amphitryon']
perseus: meliora mente concipe atque animum excita.
anceps: me^li^o_ra^ me_nte* co_nci^p(e) a_tqv(e) a^ni^m(u)m e_xci^ta*

speaker: ['#amphitryon']
perseus: aderit profecto, qualis ex omni solet
anceps: a^de^ri_t pro^fe_cto* qva_li^s e_x o*mni_ so^le*t

speaker: ['#amphitryon', '#megara']
perseus: labore, maior. Quod nimis miseri volunt
anceps: la*bo_re^ ma_jo*r qvo_d ni^mi_s mi^se^ri_ vo^lu*nt

speaker: ['#megara', '#amphitryon']
perseus: hoc facile credunt, Immo quod metuunt nimis
anceps: ho*c fa^ci^le^ cre_du*nt i_mmo^ qvo_d me^tu^u_nt ni^mi*s

speaker: ['#amphitryon']
perseus: numquam moveri posse nec tolli putant:
anceps: nu*mqva_m mo^ve_ri* po_sse^ ne_c to*lli_ pu^ta*nt

speaker: ['#amphitryon']
perseus: prona est timori semper in peius fides.
anceps: pro*n(a) e_st ti^mo_ri*s se_mpe^r i_n pe*ju_s fi^de*s

speaker: ['#megara']
perseus: Demersus ac defossus et toto insuper
anceps: de*me_rsu^s a_c de*fo_ssu^s e_t to*t(o) i_nsu^pe*r

speaker: ['#megara']
perseus: oppressus orbe quam viam ad superos habet?
anceps: o*ppre_ssu^s o_rbe* qva_m vi^(a)m a_d su^pe^ro_s ha^be*t

speaker: ['#amphitryon']
perseus: Quam tunc habebat, cum per arentem plagam
anceps: qva*m tu_nc ha^be_ba*t cu_m pe^r a_re*nte_m pla^ga*m

speaker: ['#amphitryon']
perseus: et fiuctuantes more turbati maris
anceps: e*t flu_ctu^a_nte*s mo_re^ tu_rba*ti_ ma^ri*s

speaker: ['#amphitryon']
perseus: adit harenas bisque discedens fretum
anceps: a*di_t ha^re_na*s bi_sqve^ di_sce*de_ns fre^tu*m

speaker: ['#amphitryon']
perseus: et bis recurrens, cumque deserta rate
anceps: e*t bi_s re^cu_rre*ns cu_mqve^ de_se*rta_ ra^te*

speaker: ['#amphitryon']
perseus: deprensus haesit Syrtium brevibus vadis
anceps: de*pre_nsu^s h[ae]si*t sy_rti^u_m bre^vi^bu_s va^di*s

speaker: ['#amphitryon']
perseus: et puppe fixa maria superavit pedes.
anceps: e*t pu_ppe^ fi_xa* ma^ri^a^ su^pe^ra*vi_t pe^de*s

speaker: ['#megara']
perseus: Iniqua raro maximis virtutibus
anceps: i*ni_qva^ ra_ro* ma_xi^mi_s vi*rtu_ti^bu*s

speaker: ['#megara']
perseus: fortuna parcit; nemo se tuto diu
anceps: fo*rtu_na^ pa_rci*t ne_mo^ se_ tu*to_ di^u*

speaker: ['#megara']
perseus: periculis offerre tam crebris potest:
anceps: pe*ri_cu^li_s o*ffe_rre^ ta_m cre*bri_s po^te*st

speaker: ['#megara']
perseus: quem saepe transit casus, aliquando invenit.
anceps: qve*m s[ae]pe^ tra_nsi*t ca_su^s a^li^qva*nd(o) i_nve^ni*t

speaker: ['#megara']
perseus: Sed ecce saevus ac minas vultu gerens
anceps: se*d e_cce^ s[ae]vu*s a_c mi^na_s vu*ltu_ ge^re*ns

speaker: ['#megara']
perseus: et qualis animo est, talis incessu venit
anceps: e*t qva_li^s a^ni^m(o) e*st ta_li^s i_nce*ssu_ ve^ni*t

speaker: ['#megara']
perseus: aliena dextra sceptra concutiens Lycus.
anceps: a^li^e_na^ de_xtra* sce_ptra^ co_ncu^ti^e_ns ly^cu*s

speaker: ['#lycus']
perseus: Vrbis regens opulenta Thebanae loca
anceps: u*rbi_s re^ge_ns o^pu^le_nta^ the_ba*n[ae] lo^ca*

speaker: ['#lycus']
perseus: et omne quicquid uberi cingit solo
anceps: e*t o_mne^ qvi_dqvi*d u_be^ri_s ci*ngi_t so^li*

speaker: ['#lycus']
perseus: obliqua Phocis, quicquid Ismenos rigat,
anceps: o*bli_qva^ pho_ci*s qvi_dqvi^d i_sme*no_s ri^ga*t

speaker: ['#lycus']
perseus: quicquid Cithaeron vertice excelso videt,
anceps: qvi*dqvi_d ci^th[ae]ro*n ve_rti^c(e) e_xce*lso_ vi^de*t

speaker: ['#lycus']
perseus: et bina findens Isthmos exilis freta
anceps: e*t bi_na^ fi_nde*ns i_sthmo^s e_xi*li_s fre^ta*

speaker: ['#lycus']
perseus: non vetera patriae iura possideo domus
anceps: no*n ve^te^ra^ pa^tri^[ae] ju_ra^ po_ssi^de^o_ do^mu*s

speaker: ['#lycus']
perseus: ignavus heres; nobiles non sunt mihi
anceps: i*gna_vu^s he_re*s no_bi^le_s no*n su_nt mi^hi*

speaker: ['#lycus']
perseus: avi nec altis inclitum titulis genus.
anceps: a*vi_ ne^c a_lti*s i_ncli^tu_m ti^tu^li_s ge^nu*s

speaker: ['#lycus']
perseus: sed clara virtus: qui genus iactat suum.
anceps: se*d cla_ra^ vi_rtu*s qvi_ ge^nu_s ja*cta_t su^u*m

speaker: ['#lycus']
perseus: aliena laudat, rapta sed trepida manu
anceps: a^li^e_na^ l[au]da*t ra_pta^ se_d tre^pi^da_ ma^nu*

speaker: ['#lycus']
perseus: sceptra obtinentur; omnis in ferro est salus:
anceps: sce*ptr(a) o_pti^ne_ntu*r o_mni^s i_n fe*rr(o) e_st sa^lu*s

speaker: ['#lycus']
perseus: quod civibus tenere te invitis scias.
anceps: qvo*d ci_vi^bu_s te*ne_re^ t(e) i_nvi*ti_s sci^a*s

speaker: ['#lycus']
perseus: strictus tuetur ensis, alieno in loco
anceps: stri*ctu_s tu^e_tu*r e_nsi^s a^li^e*n(o) i_n lo^co*

speaker: ['#lycus']
perseus: haut stabile regnum est; una sed nostras potest
anceps: h[au]t sta^bi^le^ re_gn(u)m e*st u_na^ se_d no*stra_s po^te*st

speaker: ['#lycus']
perseus: fundare vires iuncta regali face
anceps: fu*nda_re^ vi_re*s ju_ncta^ re_ga*li_ fa^ce*

speaker: ['#lycus']
perseus: thalamisque Megara: ducet e genere inclito
anceps: tha^la^mi_sqve^ me^ga^ra* du_ce^t e_ ge^ne^r(e) i_ncli^to*

speaker: ['#lycus']
perseus: novitas colorem nostra, non equidem reor
anceps: no^vi^ta_s co^lo_re*m no_stra^ no_n e^qvi^de_m re^o*r

speaker: ['#lycus']
perseus: fore ut recuset ac meos spernat toros;
anceps: fo*r(e) u_t re^cu_se*t a_c me^o_s spe*rna_t to^ro*s

speaker: ['#lycus']
perseus: quod si impotenti pertinax animo abnuet,
anceps: qvo*d s(i) i_mpo^te_nti* pe_rti^na_x a^ni^m(o) a_bnu^e*t

speaker: ['#lycus']
perseus: stat tollere omnem penitus Herculeam domum.
anceps: sta*t to_lle^r(e) o_mne*m pe^ni^tu^s he_rcu^le^a_m do^mu*m

speaker: ['#lycus']
perseus: invidia factum ac sermo popularis premet?
anceps: i*nui^di^a^ fa_ct(u)m a*c se_rmo^ po^pu^la*ri_s pre^me*t

speaker: ['#lycus']
perseus: ars prima regni est posse invidiam pati.
anceps: a*rs pri_ma^ re_gn(i) e*st po_ss(e) i^n i_nvi^di^a_ pa^ti*

speaker: ['#lycus']
perseus: temptemus igitur, fors dedit nobis locum.
anceps: te*mpte_mu^s i^gi^tu*r fo_rs de^di_t no*bi_s lo^cu*m

speaker: ['#lycus']
perseus: namque ipsa, tristi vestis obtentu caput
anceps: na*mqv(e) i_psa^ tri_sti* ve_sti^s o_bte*ntu_ ca^pu*t

speaker: ['#lycus']
perseus: velata, iuxta praesides adstat deos
anceps: ve*la_ta^ ju_xta* pr[ae]si^de_s a*dsta_t de^o*s

speaker: ['#lycus']
perseus: laterique adhaeret verus Alcidae sator.
anceps: la^te^ri_qv(e) a^dh[ae]re*t ve_ru^s a_lci*d[ae] sa^to*r

speaker: ['#megara']
perseus: Quidnam iste, nostri generis exitium ac lues,
anceps: qui*dn(a)m i_ste^ no_stri* ge^ne^ri^s e_xi^ti^(u)m a_c lu^e*s

speaker: ['#megara', '#lycus']
perseus: novi parat? quid temptat? O clarum trahens
anceps: no*vi_ pa^ra_t qvi*d te_mpta^t o_ cla*ru_m tra^he*ns

speaker: ['#lycus']
perseus: a stirpe nomen regia, facilis mea
anceps: a* sti_rpe^ no_me*n re_gi^a_ fa^ci^li_s me^a*

speaker: ['#lycus']
perseus: parumper aure verba patienti excipe.
anceps: pa*ru_mpe^r [au]re* ve_rba^ pa^ti^e*nt(i) e_xci^pe*

speaker: ['#lycus']
perseus: si aeterna semper odia mortales gerant
anceps: s(i) [ae]te_rna^ se_mpe*r o^di^a^ mo_rta*le_s ge^ra*nt

speaker: ['#lycus']
perseus: nec coeptus umquam cedat ex animis furor,
anceps: ne*c c[oe]ptu^s u_mqva*m ce_da^t e_x a^ni^mi_s fu^ro*r

speaker: ['#lycus']
perseus: sed arma felix teneat infelix paret,
anceps: se*d a_rma^ fe_li*x te^ne^a^t i_nfe*li_x pa^re*t

speaker: ['#lycus']
perseus: nihil relinquent bella; tum vastis ager
anceps: ni*hi_l re^li_nqve*nt be_lla^ tu_m va*sti_s a^ge*r

speaker: ['#lycus']
perseus: squalebit arvis, subdita tectis face
anceps: sqva*le_bi^t a_rvi*s su_bdi^ta_ te*cti_s fa^ce*

speaker: ['#lycus']
perseus: altus sepultas obruet gentes cinis.
anceps: a*ltu_s se^pu_lta*s o_bru^e_t ge*nte_s ci^ni*s

speaker: ['#lycus']
perseus: pacem reduci velle victori expedit,
anceps: pa*ce_m re^du_ci* ue_lle^ ui_cto*r(i) e_xpe^di*t

speaker: ['#lycus']
perseus: victo necesse est. particeps regno veni;
anceps: vi*cto_ ne^ce_ss(e) e*st pa_rti^ce_ps re*gno_ ve^ni*

speaker: ['#lycus']
perseus: sociemur animis, pignus hoc fidei cape:
anceps: so^ci^e_mu^r a^ni^mi*s pi_gnu^s ho_c fi^de^i_ ca^pe*

speaker: ['#lycus']
perseus: continge dextram, quid truci vultu siles?
anceps: co*nti_nge^ de_xtra*m qvi_d tru^ci_ vu*ltu_ si^le*s

speaker: ['#megara']
perseus: Egone ut parentis sanguine aspersam manum
anceps: e^go^n(e) u_t pa^re_nti*s sa_ngvi^n(e) a_spe*rsa_m ma^nu*m

speaker: ['#megara']
perseus: fratrumque gemina caede contingam? prius
anceps: fra*tru_mqve^ ge^mi^na* c[ae]de^ co_nti*nga_m pri^u*s

speaker: ['#megara']
perseus: extinguet ortus, referet occasus diem,
anceps: e*xti_ngve^t o_rtu*s re^fe^re^t o_cca*su_s di^e*m

speaker: ['#megara']
perseus: pax ante fida nivibus et flammis erit
anceps: pa*x a_nte^ fi_da* ni^vi^bu^s e_t fla*mmi_s e^ri*t

speaker: ['#megara']
perseus: et Scylla Siculum iunget Ausonio latus,
anceps: e*t scy_lla^ si^cu^lu*m ju_nge^t [au]so^ni^o_ la^tu*s

speaker: ['#megara']
perseus: priusque multo vicibus alternis fugax
anceps: pri*u_sqve^ mu_lto* vi^ci^bu^s a_lte*rni_s fu^ga*x

speaker: ['#megara']
perseus: Euripus unda stabit Euboica piger.
anceps: [eu]ri_pu^s u_nda* sta_bi^t [eu]bo^i^ca_ pi^ge*r

speaker: ['#megara']
perseus: patrem abstulisti, regna, germanos, larem
anceps: pa*tr(e)m a_bstu^li_sti* re_gna^ ge_rma*no_s la^re*m

speaker: ['#megara']
perseus: patrium— quid ultra est? una res superest mihi
anceps: pa^tri^u_m qvi^d u_ltr(a) e*st u_na^ re_s su^pe^re_st mi^hi*

speaker: ['#megara']
perseus: fratre ac parente carior, regno ac lare:
anceps: fra*tr(e) a_c pa^re_nte* ca_ri^o_r re*gn(o) a_c la^re*

speaker: ['#megara']
perseus: odium tui, quod esse cum populo mihi
anceps: o^di^u_m tu^i_ qvo*d e_sse^ cu_m po^pu^lo_ mi^hi*

speaker: ['#megara']
perseus: commune doleo: pars quota ex illo mea est?
anceps: co*mmu_ne^ do^le^o* pa_rs qvo^t(a) e_x i*sto_ me^(a) e*st

speaker: ['#megara']
perseus: dominare tumidus, spiritus altos gere:
anceps: do^mi^na_re^ tu^mi^du*s spi_ri^tu_s a*lto_s ge^re*

speaker: ['#megara']
perseus: sequitur superbos ultor a tergo deus.
anceps: se^qvi^tu_r su^pe_rbo*s u_lto^r a_ te*rgo_ de^u*s

speaker: ['#megara']
perseus: Thebana novi regna: quid matres loquar
anceps: the*ba_na^ no_vi* re_gna^ qvi_d ma*tre_s lo^qva*r

speaker: ['#megara']
perseus: passas et ausas scelera? quid geminum nefas
anceps: pa*ssa_s e^t [au]sa*s sce^le^ra^ qvi_d ge^mi^nu_m ne^fa*s

speaker: ['#megara']
perseus: mixtumque nomen coniugis nati patris?
anceps: mi*xtu_mqve^ no_me*n co_nju^gi_s gna*ti_ pa^tri*s

speaker: ['#megara']
perseus: quid bina fratrum castra? quid totidem rogos?
anceps: qvi*d bi_na^ fra_tru*m ca_stra^ qvi_d to^ti^de_m ro^go*s

speaker: ['#megara']
perseus: riget superba Tantalis luctu parens
anceps: ri*ge_t su^pe_rbo* ta_nta^li_s lu*ctu_ pa^re*ns

speaker: ['#megara']
perseus: maestusque Phrygio manat in Sipylo lapis.
anceps: m[ae]stu_sqve^ phry^gi^o* ma_na^t i_n si^py^lo_ la^pi*s

speaker: ['#megara']
perseus: quin ipse torvum subrigens crista caput
anceps: qvi*n i_pse^ to_rvu*m su_bri^ge_ns cri*sta_ ca^pu*t

speaker: ['#megara']
perseus: Illyrica Cadmus regna permensus fuga
anceps: i*lly^ri^ca^ ca_dmu*s re_gna^ pe_rme*nsu_s fu^ga*

speaker: ['#megara']
perseus: longas reliquit corporis tracti notas.
anceps: lo*nga_s re^li_qvi*t co_rpo^ri_s tra*cti_ no^ta*s

speaker: ['#megara']
perseus: haec te manent exempla: dominare ut libet,
anceps: h[ae]c te_ ma^ne_nt e*xe_mpla^ do^mi^na*r(e) u_t li^be*t

speaker: ['#megara']
perseus: dum solita regni fata te nostri vocent
anceps: du*m so^li^ta^ re_gni* fa_ta^ te_ no*stri_ vo^ce*nt

speaker: ['#lycus']
perseus: Agedum efferatas rabida voces amove
anceps: a^ge^d(u)m e_ffe^ra_ta*s ra^bi^da^ vo_ce*s a_mo^ve*

speaker: ['#lycus']
perseus: et disce regum imperia ab Alcide pati
anceps: e*t di_sce^ re_g(u)m i*mpe^ri^(a) a^b a_lci*de_ pa^ti*

speaker: ['#lycus']
perseus: ego rapta quamvis sceptra victrici geram
anceps: e^go^ ra_pta^ qva_mvi*s sce_ptra^ vi_ctri*ci_ ge^ra*m

speaker: ['#lycus']
perseus: dextra regamque cuncta sine legum metu
anceps: de*xtra_ re^ga_mqve* cu_ncta^ si^ne^ le*gu_m me^tu*

speaker: ['#lycus']
perseus: quas arma vincunt, pauca pro causa loquar
anceps: qva*s a_rma^ vi_ncu*nt p[au]ca^ pro_ c[au]sa_ lo^qva*r

speaker: ['#lycus']
perseus: nostra, cruento cecidit in bello pater?
anceps: no*stra_ cru^e_nto* ce^ci^di^t i_n be*llo_ pa^te*r

speaker: ['#lycus']
perseus: cecidere fratres? arma non servant modum;
anceps: ce^ci^de_re^ fra_tre*s a_rma^ no_n se*rva_nt mo^du*m

speaker: ['#lycus']
perseus: nec temperari facile nec reprimi potest
anceps: ne*c te_mpe^ra_ri* fa^ci^le^ ne_c re^pri^mi_ po^te*st

speaker: ['#lycus']
perseus: stricti ensis ira, bella delectat cruor.
anceps: stri*ct(i) e_nsi^s i_ra* be_lla^ de_le*cta_t cru^o*r

speaker: ['#lycus']
perseus: sed ille regno pro suo, nos improba
anceps: se*d i_lle^ re_gno* pro_ su^o_ no*s i_mpro^ba*
